5: Carbina, where are you off to?
9:
I got a call from HQ. I might run late
tonight.
18:
Who knows. But I'm not expecting it
to be a pleasant chat.
21:
Hmm... Is there anything I can do to
help?
25:
No. I'm sorry, I was just grumbling to
myself. These things happen when
you work for a big company.
28: Yeah... Okay, well, take care then.
33:
I will. And I'll do everything in my
power to protect Starview and
everyone in it.
38:
Argh, these nerves... I'm more on
edge than when I go up against
actual criminals.
40: Oh well. Nowhere to go but forward.
43:
There you are. Apologies for calling
you so suddenly.
45:
An order is an order, sir. How can I
be of use?
48:
It's about your undercover case. The
investigation seems to be going
well, but I had some issues with this
report.
50:
It's factual, of that there's no doubt,
but I still find that it's somewhat...
lacking. Would you agree?
53:
Yes. That would be because the
targets have realized the purpose of
my mission.
56:
If I were to add further details into
the report, it would only raise their
suspicions to untenable levels.
59:
They "realized" it? Or did you reveal it
to them yourself?
61:
The latter, sir. I deemed it to be the
best course of action for the
purposes of my mission.
65:
I can understand why you made
that decision.
71:
However, as you know, the
submission of inaccurate or
incomplete reports subjects you to
a penalty.
73:
There's even the likelihood this could
hurt your chances at a promotion.
74:
Wouldn't this get in the way of your
dream? You wanted to do
everything you can to protect
people, no?
76:
Listen. I'm willing to overlook this,
provided you submit an amended
report now. What do you say?
82:
Respectfully, I will not be amending
the report, sir. I believe it currently
contains all the information I have
to disclose.
86:
You're a talented soldier, Carbina.
The people trust you, and you even
command your own squadron.
87:
You made it this far because you
followed your dreams.
88:
Are you really going to abandon
them now?
91:
To commit an act I'm not proud of in
front of someone like you, sir, would
be in direct violation of my
dream.
94:
I see. Well, if you understand what
the consequences are, I suppose I'll
have no choice but to give you a
lower evaluation. Though...
97:
I wonder if dinging you for such a
small infraction would just be
missing the bigger picture...
100:
Diligence in report writing is one of
our directives, yes, but so is the
successful completion of a mission.
101:
The purpose of report-making is to
provide oversight for the mission,
and ensure no mistakes are made
along the way that could lead to
failure.
103:
It might be best, in this case, to give
you the benefit of the doubt, and
re-evaluate this case once the
mission is complete.
108:
It's for the sake of the mission that I
do this. That will be all. Dismissed.
119:
I made it out this time... But how
much longer can I keep this up?
126: Thank you. It... went surprisingly well.
129:
Really? Well, that's good. Say, if
you're tired and up for a snack, I've
got some sweets you could try!
139:
Fine, I'll take one. I guess I deserve to
treat myself a bit, considering how
smoothly things went.
142:
So, we don't need to do anything
about that situation?
146: No. You can leave it all to me.
149:
I got past this hurdle, and I'll do the
same next time. And the next time.
151: I'll keep this going as long as I can.
